<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9bf6e84-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s316i"><num value="316i">§ 316i.</num><heading> Assignment of leases</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The lessee may, with the approval of the Secretary, assign in whole or in part any lease, and to the extent of such assignment be relieved from any liability in respect of such lease, accruing subsequent to the effective date of such assignment.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9bf6e85-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-03-04/ch513/s10">Mar. 4, 1927, ch. 513, § 10</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1453">44 Stat. 1453</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9bf6e86-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9bf6e87-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
